H0.text: The number ten raised to the power of one hundred is known by what name. Megatron

H1.text: The number ten raised to the power of one hundred is known by what name. Centillion

H2.text: The number ten raised to the power of one hundred is known by what name. Decamillion

H3.text: The number ten raised to the power of one hundred is known by what name. Googal

A4.text: A googol is the large number 10^100 or ten to the power of one hundred.

A5.text: A googol is approximately equal to 70! ≈ 1.1979 × 10^100.

A6.text: The term was coined in 1920 by 9-year-old Milton Sirotta (1911–1981), nephew of American mathematician Edward Kasner.

A7.text: A googol is considerably smaller than a centillion.
